headline: CoreWeave debut, PayPal falls, Nippon-US Steel deal: Market Minute
summary: Here are some of the stocks on the move Friday, March 28. CoreWeave (CRWV) shares started trading at $39, below the $40 initial offering price. PayPal (PYPL) is trading lower after a European lawmaker indicated the EU could charge the company fees if trade talks fall through.  Nippon Steel (5401.T) and US Steel (X) are talking to the Trump administration in hopes of reviving their merger, according to a report from Semafor. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: PayPal's shares slide as EU lawmaker raises prospect of new fees amid trade tensions
summary: (Reuters) -PayPal's shares fell 5% on Friday after comments from a European Union lawmaker raised concerns that payments firms could get swept up in escalating trade tensions and potential tariffs between the U.S. and Europe.  Earlier this week, U.S. President Donald Trump said larger tariffs could be placed on the European Union and Canada if they both work together "to do economic harm to the USA."  "In the case of digital service providers, there is also a huge economic interest on the part of U.S. companies," said Bernd Lange, the head of the European Parliament's international trade committee.

headline: Berlin on measures against U.S. tech giants: 'Nothing is off the table'
summary: BERLIN (Reuters) -A German government spokesperson said on Friday that "nothing is off the table" with regards to punitive measures in response to the threat of U.S. tariffs, after an EU lawmaker suggested they target U.S. tech giants.  "Decisions must be made jointly and in consideration of the costs and benefits within the European Union and under the leadership of the European Commission - this process is underway," he added.  U.S. President Donald Trump on Wednesday announced a 25% tariff on vehicles imported into the U.S., a move with far-reaching implications for Germany's car industry, especially Volkswagen, which has a large supply base in Mexico.

headline: EU could charge fees on PayPal in U.S. tariff dispute, says senior lawmaker
summary: BERLIN (Reuters) -     The European Union could charge fees on PayPal (PYPL) as part of a tariff dispute with the United States, a senior European lawmaker said on Friday.
